    {
      "id": "sybil_2_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_2",
      "description": "Offering a driver-focused 997.1 Carrera powered by the 3.6L M96 flat-six. This example is mechanically sound, featuring a documented IMS bearing retrofit and rear main seal replacement. The G97 six-speed manual transaxle provides precise engagement, delivering power to the rear wheels via a limited-slip differential. The suspension geometry is dialed in with Porsche Active Suspension Management (PASM), ensuring flat cornering and high lateral grip. Recent service includes a full cooling system overhaul and new ignition coils. While the exterior shows minor road-derived patina, the structural integrity and drivetrain performance remain exceptional. This is a high-functioning, analog sports car ready for the canyons.",
